      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): avoid silent truncation in partial streaming finals",
        "body": "Fixes an intermittent Telegram partial-streaming failure mode where a streamed final could be marked as delivered before any follow-up chunks are actually sent.\\n\\nWhen a follow-up send fails, the channel code can otherwise suppress the visible error fallback (because deliveryState already says delivered), leaving the user with a mid-sentence cutoff.\\n\\nChanges:\\n- Telegram: only mark streamed finals delivered after follow-up chunks are sent successfully; add regression tests.\\n- Telegram: when a preview-finalized final looks truncated, try to repair it by reading the transcript-backed canonical final and editing the Telegram message to the longer text.\\n- Diagnostics: avoid aborting queued embedded work when the session is still processing queued items (reduces false-positive stuck aborts).\\n\\nRelated: #49889 (Telegram partial-stream finalization delivery-state ambiguity / message-loss incidents).",
